Shoutout to the real MVPs in our lives - our moms. 

I remember the day I finally walked across that graduation stage in Huntsville, Alabama. I was 30 years old, already a proud father of two amazing kids - a five-year-old and a three-year-old. But you know what's the kicker? My mom was there cheering me on like I'd graduated right on time with all the 20-somethings.

She drove a whopping 770 miles just to witness that moment. I mean, come on! Can you believe it? I was 30 with two kids, and my mom was ecstatic as if I'd just completed high school.

Here's the deal, before I wrap this up - you've got to appreciate your mom, or whoever played that role in your life. They went through so much to bring you into this world. They had dreams and hopes for you, and they made sacrifices you might never fully understand.

So, when you're out there making choices, whether they're cool, serious, or a little bit of both, remember the love and sacrifice that brought you here. Let's hear it for the unsung heroes of our lives - our moms.
